#### Syntax

```
GET key
```


GET returns the value as a string for the key in args.

The command returns an empty string if the key does not exist.
	

#### Examples

```

localhost:7379> SET k1 v1
OK
localhost:7379> GET k1
OK "v1"
localhost:7379> GET k2
OK ""
	
```
